                          <header>
                                        <h1 id="page-title">
              	Libraries and Archives              </h1>
                        
			
                      </header>
                
		
        <div id="content">
        	        				  <div class="region region-content">
    <div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">
  <div class="block-inner clearfix">
                <div class="block-content content">
      <article id="article-5396" class="article article-type-page clearfix" role="article">

  
      
  
  <div class="article-content">
  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><!--
<div><p><strong><span style="color:#FF0000;">Holiday Closure: The Main Library &amp; Archives, and the H.H. Mu Far Eastern Library will be closed to the public from Wednesday, December 23, 2015 to Friday, January 1, 2016.</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Regular hours for both libraries (Monday to Friday, 10:00 am to 5:00 pm) will resume on Monday, January 4, 2016.</strong></p>
</div>
<div>
<hr /></div>
<p>--></p>
<p><img alt="[scent free environment]" src="/sites/default/files/imce/library-scent-free.jpg" style="width: 100px; float: right; height: 100px" /></p>
<div>
<p>The Royal Ontario Museum (ROM) Libraries &amp; Archives are open to the general public each weekday, except holidays.&nbsp; As reference libraries, our collections are <strong>non-circulating</strong>, materials are strictly in-library use only.</p>
<p>As part of the University of Toronto Library system, the ROM library holdings can be found through the <a href="http://library.utoronto.ca" target="_blank">University of Toronto online catalogue.</a></p>
<p>The ROM Libraries &amp; Archives are <strong>scent-free environments</strong>, please refrain from using scented personal products when you come visit us.&nbsp; We thank you for sharing the air.</p>
</div>
<!-- relocated to Library News/New Acquisitions
	<p><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/fqGV-oEOYtE" width="420"></iframe></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>--></p>
<table border="0" style="width: 100%">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 150px; vertical-align: top"><a href="http://www.rom.on.ca/en/collections-research/library-archives/main-library-archives"><strong>Main Library</strong></a><br />
			<img alt="[Sackler Reading Room, Main Library]" src="/sites/default/files/imce/library-main-rom2004_990_1.jpg" style="width: 150px; float: left; height: 116px" /></td>
<td style="width: 450px; vertical-align: top">
<ul>
<li>hours: <span style="color: #b22222"><strong>Monday-Friday, 10 am-5 pm</strong></span></li>
<li>access: via Museum entrance on Bloor Street</li>
<li>collection focus:
<ul>
<li>arts &amp; archaeology of western cultures and of aboriginal peoples of North America</li>
<li>earth sciences - geology, geochronology, mineralogy</li>
<li>life sciences - botany, entomology, herpetology, ichthyology, mammalogy, ornithology, zoology</li>
<li>palaeontology</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" style="width: 100%">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 150px; vertical-align: top"><a href="http://www.rom.on.ca/en/collections-research/rom-library-archives/hh-mu-far-eastern-library"><strong>Far Eastern Library</strong></a><br />
			<img alt="Far Eastern Library" height="98" src="/sites/default/files/imce/library-fel-rom2006_8875_3.jpg" style="float: left" width="150" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 450px; vertical-align: top">
<ul>
<li>hours: <span style="color: #b22222"><strong>Monday-Friday, 10 am-5 pm</strong></span></li>
<li>access: via Museum staff entrance on south side of ROM building</li>
<li>collection focus:
<ul>
<li>arts &amp; archaeology of Asian, Egyptian, Near &amp; Middle Eastern cultures</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Note: the library may close from time to time because of short-staffing, please call ahead (<strong>416-586-5718 ext.3)</strong> for materials to be retrieved for use in the Main Library.&nbsp; Immediate retrieval and delivery cannot be assured.</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" style="width: 100%">
